  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Eco friendly Agriculture in Tamil Nadu with Enterprise model</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Eco-veg-SAAL project was implemented with Christian Aid support for the last two years, however, to make it a sustainable enterprise model, this project will be further supported for two more years.  In the next two years project to work with 6000 small farmers and train them on organic cultivation which will support them in receiving organic certification from the government for better pricing of vegetables.  It is expected that farmers income may go up by 30-40% which would help in sustainable livelihood.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Train and support 6,000 farmers (including 3,000 women and 2,400 farmers from excluded communities) on sustainable, organic agricultural techniques, and enable them to increase their income by  40%. By increasing yields, and linking producers and consumers, this project will ensure each target farmer will earn INR 350-500 per day, which will ensure they can make an economically viable livelihood from  organic farming. To use cutting-edge technology to support 10 sourcing centres to serve us central hub.	To train farmers in natural methods of crop production and supply them with organic seeds suitable for their location, increasing yields. To bring multiple producers together so farmers can set fair prices for produce while guaranteeing a varied, plentiful supply for vendors</narrative>
  </description>
